This directory contains the source code for an experimental LLMNR responder for
GNU/Linux operating systems.  It is intended to be used on a small/home network
to improve interoperability between GNU/Linux and Microsoft Windows.

This program is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify it under
the terms of the GNU General Public License.  You should have got a copy of it
in the COPYING file.

For generic installation instructions, see the INSTALL file.  If you have got a
copy of this program from our repository, you must generate a configure script
and Makefile templates with GNU autoconf and GNU automake once before you begin
installation.

See our wiki at <https://bitbucket.org/kazssym/xllmnrd/wiki> for more
information.
